But depleted uranium was a whole other matter, it was certainly much more sturdier than the previous houses they had broken into.

The wolf still outside, looked up at the house, and thought about how to get in. They blew on the doors, the outside walls, and even tried scratching the windows, all seemingly resistant to his claws and might. He tried climbing up the house, but found himself loosing his grip and unable to reach the roof. The wolf was getting frustrated, he had usually entered a past household by now. 

The wolf decided to try a different approach. He saw the ground, and dug deep into the dirt. Surely he could tunnel into the house if he could not break down its doors, he thought. But upon digging deep into the soil, he struck the house's foundation, and found that it too was made up of depleted uranium. Drat, the wolf thought, he was not going to get into the house. The wolf then decided to head elsewhere, hoping to find a home they could break into, one that was not made of depleted uranium.

Sure enough, the 92nd little pig woke up early next morning, feeling very refreshed. They slept soundly, and noted that the wolf had failed on entering their home.
